paragraph: 1. KLHL14, a member of the Kelch-like family, is implicated in the organization of microtubules and actin filaments, which are critical for maintaining cellular structure and integrity. It may also play a role in protein ubiquitination, targeting specific substrates for degradation and thus modulating protein levels within the cell.
keyword: ("KLHL14") AND ("cytoskeleton" OR "protein ubiquitination" OR "cellular integrity") AND (hasabstract[text]) AND humans[mh] NOT Retracted Publication[pt]
